@* The RE-PARAMETERISED consumer of CascadeIsFixed.razor's cascade: its own [Parameter] Tag changes
   on every click, so Blazor re-parameterises it and re-supplies the supplier's LIVE value -- it
   advances 1 -> 2 -> 3 under a FIXED cascade. It is this consumer that refutes the obvious
   "freeze the value at mount" implementation. Compiles perfectly well on its own. *@
<span id="b">@Level</span>

@code {
    [Parameter] public string Tag { get; set; } = "";
    [CascadingParameter] public int Level { get; set; }
}
